OL,6,FShe maintained during the trial he had
OL,7,Fstabbed himself, but the pathologist
OL,8,Fwho carried out the postmortem had
OL,9,Fconcerns how a right-handed man could
OL,10,Finflict a wound to their own chest at
OL,11,Fsuch an angle, and with such extreme
OL,12,Fforce to fracture three ribs `
OL,13,Fcompletely severing one.
OL,15,FIt is believed in a drunken temper,
OL,16,FWronska took the knife and stabbed her
OL,17,Fpartner.
OL,19,FShe was sentenced to life
OL,20,Fimprisonment, with a minimum term of
OL,21,F16 years.
